@stayreadyto3dprint I'm not annoyed at you using it, I'm annoyed at Bambu using it.  They invented security issues that did not exist.  They pointed to a sketchy article about a "hacker" remotely starting a bunch of printers.  They stated "hackers" were constantly attacking their cloud.  

They're responsible for the security of their cloud and it should have nothing to do with my printer.  I understand the laser argument, but only slightly because developer mode bypasses all of that.

There is absolutely zero reason why we shouldn't retain the ability to remotely monitor our printers in developer mode.
